e Peak<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive:<\/strong> From Nelson, drive 14.5 km east on 3A and turn left (north) on Sitkum Creek FSR at Nine Mile. Zero odometer.<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>0.0<\/strong><br \/>\n14 km on rough Sitkum Creek FSR. <\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Turn left onto Kane or Granger Road and continue to the Alpine Road (4WD) and the old Alpine Mine at the base of Mt Cornfield. The road has been<\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> blockaded at about 10-11kms. It was unmaintained and had so much deadfall, that it must be walked anyway. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Route from the mine:<\/strong> A 30-minute scramble takes you up to the first peak 7730\u2019 816-033 on the east end of the \u201cCornfield Ridge\u201d. Descend 200\u2019 and follow the undulating, corniced ridge in a northwesterly direction for about 1.25km to the summit of Mt Cornfield, the furthest peak on the ridge. Tricky parts are classified as B2.5.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>MOUNT CORNFIELD\u00a0\u00a0 2543m\u00a0\u00a0 7750\u2019 This area has many nice ridge hikes with good views. It is close to Nelson geographically but a long way through the bush &#8211; not only a long rough drive but then an 11 km long &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2017\/11\/01\/mount-cornfield\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id":0,"_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content":false,"_jetpa